02:09.520 --> 02:11.174
MAN:
Hello, Mr. Davis.

02:12.915 --> 02:14.612
Sorry to keep you waiting.

02:19.922 --> 02:21.184
STEVE:
I'm sorry, just...

02:21.228 --> 02:23.404
you said what

02:23.447 --> 02:24.492
Seventeen.

02:24.535 --> 02:26.755
STEVE:
17 fire code violations?

02:26.798 --> 02:27.973
You sure about that?

02:28.017 --> 02:29.192
STEVE: I don't...
That doesn't make

02:29.236 --> 02:30.672
any sense.
How... What do you mean?

02:30.715 --> 02:32.239
Yeah, are we talking
about the same place?

02:32.282 --> 02:35.067
Chinatown, small little
Italian restaurant? Very small.

02:35.111 --> 02:36.243
The one you're trying
to renovate?

02:36.286 --> 02:37.418
Yeah.
Yes.

02:37.461 --> 02:39.071
STEVE: You mean small
infractions, right?

02:39.115 --> 02:40.943
Like... like a dead battery
in a smoke detector,

02:40.986 --> 02:42.597
the exit sign you can't see
'cause there's

02:42.640 --> 02:44.338
a thing over it or whatever?

02:44.381 --> 02:46.557
Well, those are both issues,
but you've got bigger problems,

02:46.601 --> 02:48.080
starting with
your electrical work.

02:48.124 --> 02:50.213
Whoa. What-what-what's wrong
with the electrical system?

02:50.257 --> 02:51.562
For one thing,
your breaker panel's

02:51.606 --> 02:53.042
dangerously overloaded.

02:53.085 --> 02:55.436
You've got open splices
in the ceiling,

02:55.479 --> 02:56.872
frayed wires
in the weather-head.

02:56.915 --> 02:58.221
It's a mess.

02:58.265 --> 02:59.788
I don't know what to say.

02:59.831 --> 03:01.529
You know whose fault this is?

03:01.572 --> 03:03.095
Yes, I do-- Uncle Vito.

03:03.139 --> 03:05.097
Yours, not Uncle Vito's.
Your fault.

03:05.141 --> 03:06.577
What do you mean, mine?

03:06.621 --> 03:08.362
Uncle Vito has been
systematically trying

03:08.405 --> 03:10.015
to destroy our dream
since he landed here.

03:10.059 --> 03:11.234
How is this
my fault?

03:11.278 --> 03:12.279
DANNY:
Well, it's your
fault because

03:12.322 --> 03:13.758
you gave him the number to use

03:13.802 --> 03:15.107
for the electrician.
That's why it's your fault.

03:15.151 --> 03:16.413
He's a great guy,
and he's-he's a great...

03:16.457 --> 03:18.110
Look at the... look at the work
he did in here.

03:18.154 --> 03:19.416
This place was
torn apart by bullets.

03:19.460 --> 03:21.549
Look at it--
it's perfect.

03:21.592 --> 03:23.246
Excuse me.
Did you say

03:23.290 --> 03:27.207
the same electricians also did
the work on these offices?

03:27.250 --> 03:28.991
What?

03:29.034 --> 03:30.601
Was that work permitted?

03:30.645 --> 03:33.256
He'll tell you.Well, I mean...

03:33.300 --> 03:35.215
FIRE INSPECTOR:
I think I need to look around.

03:36.477 --> 03:38.261
Are you stupid?
What's the matter with you?

03:38.305 --> 03:40.263
It just came out. I...When your brain stops working,

03:40.307 --> 03:41.438
you should shut your mouth.

03:43.310 --> 03:44.485
Hi.
Hi. Please...

03:44.528 --> 03:45.834
please tell me you have
something to, uh,

03:45.877 --> 03:47.444
take me away
from this situation.

03:47.488 --> 03:48.967
Actually, yeah, I do.
There's a man downstairs

03:49.011 --> 03:50.055
who wants to talk to you.

03:50.099 --> 03:51.840
All right. We know
what it's about?

03:51.883 --> 03:53.755
Saying it's about your father.

03:53.798 --> 03:56.192
My father?

03:56.236 --> 03:57.280
DAVIS:
You had yourself

03:57.324 --> 03:59.239
quite a career, didn't you?

03:59.282 --> 04:01.545
Yeah, it was something.
I mean, I'm just proud

04:01.589 --> 04:03.504
I was able to serve
my country, you know?

04:03.547 --> 04:04.635
It was an honor.

04:04.679 --> 04:06.550
How about you, Mr. Davis?

04:07.595 --> 04:08.639
Leroy.

04:08.683 --> 04:09.814
Okay.

04:09.858 --> 04:12.469
I... I did one tour in Vietnam.

04:12.513 --> 04:14.515
Oh, is that how
you knew my father?

04:14.558 --> 04:16.212
No, sir.

04:16.256 --> 04:18.214
You guys work together?

04:20.912 --> 04:24.829
I guess you could say
we knew each other through work.

04:24.873 --> 04:27.354
But did we
work together?

04:27.397 --> 04:29.573
No.

04:31.096 --> 04:34.448
I was employed by the
Hawaiian Syndicate

04:34.491 --> 04:36.841
in the '70s and '80s.

04:43.108 --> 04:45.937
I'm sorry, did you just, uh...

04:45.981 --> 04:49.201
did you just tell me you were
involved in organized crime?

04:49.245 --> 04:51.291
I painted houses.

04:51.334 --> 04:53.162
Not literally, of course.

04:53.205 --> 04:54.685
I know what the term means.

04:54.729 --> 04:56.252
You were a hit man?

04:56.296 --> 04:57.471
That's right.

04:57.514 --> 04:59.386
And yet somehow
you're sitting in my office

04:59.429 --> 05:02.171
instead of a six-by-eight cell
somewhere. How's that?

05:02.214 --> 05:04.216
I was very careful.

05:04.260 --> 05:05.348
Mmm.

05:05.392 --> 05:07.176
It also helped
that there were

05:07.219 --> 05:08.873
so many corrupt cops

05:08.917 --> 05:11.136
during the years
that I was active.

05:11.180 --> 05:13.574
The guys that weren't,
well, they were

05:13.617 --> 05:15.880
too scared to
come after me.

05:15.924 --> 05:18.274
Except for one.

05:18.318 --> 05:20.102
My father.

05:20.145 --> 05:22.496
Day I met him...

05:22.539 --> 05:25.368
I knew he was going
to be trouble.

05:33.028 --> 05:36.292
[chatter continues;
disco music playing]

06:08.193 --> 06:10.108
Next one's in you.

06:12.850 --> 06:14.374
Hey!

06:14.417 --> 06:15.723
You hear what I said?

06:15.766 --> 06:17.333
Yeah.

06:17.377 --> 06:18.943
And I don't doubt
you're telling the truth.

06:18.987 --> 06:20.423
You already killed
one cop this week.

06:20.467 --> 06:22.294
You seem to think you know
something about me.

06:22.338 --> 06:24.296
My name's John McGarrett.

06:24.340 --> 06:27.082
Detective John McGarrett.

06:27.125 --> 06:28.953
I'm the guy that's going
to put you in jail

06:28.997 --> 06:30.128
for the rest of your life.

06:30.172 --> 06:32.957
I guess he was wrong about that.

06:33.001 --> 06:35.307
He was right about the
other thing, though.

06:35.351 --> 06:39.399
I did kill Detective Ozuki
earlier that week.

06:39.442 --> 06:43.098
All this that you're telling me,
if all of this is true...

06:43.141 --> 06:45.143
why you coming forward now?

06:45.187 --> 06:47.798
I'm an old man.

06:47.842 --> 06:50.497
Been carrying this
around long enough.

06:51.846 --> 06:55.153
If your father was here,
I'd be doing this with him.

06:55.197 --> 06:59.462
But since he's not,
well, I figure...

06:59.506 --> 07:02.334
you're the next best option.

07:02.378 --> 07:04.293
So...

07:11.518 --> 07:14.129
Shall we get on with it?

07:16.523 --> 07:18.916
Go on. Open it.

07:30.972 --> 07:33.409
How'd you get this
past my security?

07:33.453 --> 07:34.802
Like I said,

07:34.845 --> 07:36.499
I'm very careful.

07:36.543 --> 07:37.848
Are these yours?

07:37.892 --> 07:39.415
They were.

07:39.459 --> 07:42.505
But now they're evidence.

07:42.549 --> 07:45.247
Commander McGarrett,
I'd like to confess

07:45.290 --> 07:49.773
to the murder
of Detective Jake Ozuki.

07:51.688 --> 07:53.864
And 17 others.

07:56.301 --> 07:59.566
[Hawaii Five-O
theme song plays]

08:29.944 --> 08:32.424
LEROY:
About 30 yards

08:32.468 --> 08:34.383
on the left,
you turn there.

08:34.426 --> 08:36.690
There's a dirt road.

08:40.520 --> 08:44.001
If you have something to say,
Commander, say it.

08:45.873 --> 08:48.571
Whatever it is
you're doing today...

08:50.007 --> 08:52.140
I don't know whether you're
trying to make amends

08:52.183 --> 08:54.142
or you're looking for
some kind of atonement...

08:55.709 --> 08:57.667
...but if that's it,
you're way off.

08:57.711 --> 08:59.277
Way off, all right?

08:59.321 --> 09:02.280
You should know you
sealed your fate...

09:03.412 --> 09:05.066
...the first time
you pulled the trigger

09:05.109 --> 09:07.111
and took an innocent life.

09:10.027 --> 09:11.986
I know.

09:18.253 --> 09:20.255
Adam Noshimuri,
got a minute?

09:20.298 --> 09:22.344
Not really.Won't take long.

09:22.387 --> 09:23.693
Just a few follow-up questions.

09:23.737 --> 09:24.999
No, I've
given you enough

09:25.042 --> 09:26.435
of my time already,
Agent McNeal.

09:26.478 --> 09:27.784
I got somewhere to be.Okay.

09:27.828 --> 09:28.959
Why don't I ride with you?

09:29.003 --> 09:30.221
We can talk on the way.

09:31.266 --> 09:32.484
Yeah, that's not gonna happen.

09:32.528 --> 09:33.790
Don't make this difficult, okay?

09:33.834 --> 09:35.792
Or what

09:35.836 --> 09:39.143
You got nothing to hold me on,
and you know it.

09:39.187 --> 09:40.492
I'll see you around.

09:40.536 --> 09:42.146
I'm trying real hard
to be professional

09:42.190 --> 09:44.279
about this, but you're
not making it easy.

09:47.674 --> 09:49.284
Get in the car.

09:55.769 --> 09:57.335
♪ Yo, yo, yo, yo

09:57.379 --> 09:59.424
♪ Here we are

10:00.730 --> 10:03.994
